com.b2international.snowowl.datastore.server.cdo

Interface ICDOConflictProcessor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractCDOConflictProcessor, NullCDOConflictProcessor, SnomedCDOConflictProcessor

    public interface ICDOConflictProcessor
    Handles conflicting changes when synchronizing branches.

      • getRepositoryUuid

        String getRepositoryUuid()
        Returns the conflict processor's associated repository identifier.

      • addedInSource

        Object addedInSource(org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.revision.CDORevision sourceRevision,
                     Map<org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.id.CDOID,Object> targetMap)
        Checks if the specified CDORevision from the source change set conflicts with any changes on the target.
        Parameters:
        sourceRevision - the new CDORevision from the source change set
        targetMap - the computed change set for the target branch, indexed by CDOID
        Returns:
        • null if the add should be ignored;
        • a CDORevision if an addition should take place;
        • a CDOID if an object should be removed;
        • a DefaultCDOMerger.Conflict if a merge conflict should be reported.

      • changedInSourceAndTargetSingleValued

        org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.revision.delta.CDOFeatureDelta changedInSourceAndTargetSingleValued(org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.revision.delta.CDOFeatureDelta targetFeatureDelta,
                                                                                               org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.revision.delta.CDOFeatureDelta sourceFeatureDelta)
        Checks if the specified CDOFeatureDelta from the target change set conflicts with the corresponding CDOFeatureDelta on the source.
        Parameters:
        targetFeatureDelta - the single-value change on the target
        sourceFeatureDelta - the single-value change on the source
        Returns:
        • null if a conflict should be reported;
        • a CDOFeatureDelta containing the "winning" change otherwise.

      • changedInTargetAndDetachedInSource

        Object changedInTargetAndDetachedInSource(org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.revision.delta.CDORevisionDelta targetDelta)
        Checks if the object with the removed CDOID from the target change set conflicts with an item in the source change set.
        Parameters:
        targetDelta - the computed change on the target branch for the object removed on the source branch
        Returns:
        • null if the add should be ignored;
        • a CDORevision if an addition should take place;
        • a CDOID if an object should be removed;
        • a DefaultCDOMerger.Conflict if a merge conflict should be reported.

      • postProcess

        void postProcess(org.eclipse.emf.cdo.transaction.CDOTransaction transaction)
          throws ConflictException
        Post-processes the resulting change set. This usually removes cross-references from objects queued for removal before detaching them from the persistent object graph, using the specified transaction.
        Parameters:
        transaction - the CDO transaction after the change set has been applied (may not be null)
        Throws:
        ConflictException - if conflicts are detected while post-processing takes place (can be specific to a terminology, not necessarily tied to a CDO revision or delta)
